(41, 1, 32, 40, 8, 16, 16, 'them that were possessed with devils', 'Healing and Deliverance Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bringing those who are sick and possessed to Jesus for healing. The mention of casting out spirits and healing the sick in Matthew parallels the gathering of the diseased and possessed in Mark, highlighting a shared theme of Jesus'' miraculous works.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 32, 40, 4, 24, 24, 'all that were diseased, and them that were possessed with devils', 'Healing and Deliverance Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of sick individuals and those possessed with devils. They highlight the widespread need for healing and the response of the people bringing the afflicted to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 32, 41, 3, 2, 2, NULL, 'Healing on the Sabbath', 'Both passages emphasize the act of healing, with the first showing Jesus healing the diseased and the second focusing on the scrutiny of his healing on the Sabbath. This connection highlights the tension between Jesus'' healing ministry and the religious authorities'' expectations regarding the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 32, 42, 4, 40, 40, 'when the sun did set', 'Healing at Sunset', 'Both passages emphasize the time of day, ''when the sun did set'' and ''when the sun was setting,'' as a significant moment for healing. They describe the act of bringing the sick to Jesus, highlighting his role as a healer.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 32, 41, 1, 21, 21, NULL, 'Healing and Teaching in Capernaum', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' activities in Capernaum, highlighting his role as a teacher and healer. The mention of the Sabbath in the second passage sets the stage for the healing that occurs later in the evening.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 33, 41, 1, 5, 5, 'all the city was gathered together', 'Gathering of the People', 'Both passages emphasize a significant gathering of people. In Mark 1:33, the city gathers at the door, while in Mark 1:5, all of Judea and Jerusalem come to John for baptism.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 33, 44, 13, 44, 44, 'all the city was gathered together', 'Gathering of the City', 'This connection highlights the theme of community gathering in both passages. In Mark, the city gathers at the door, while in Acts, almost the whole city comes together to hear the word of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 34, 42, 4, 41, 41, 'cast out many devils', 'Connection of Healing and Demons', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of many and the casting out of devils. They highlight Jesus'' authority over sickness and evil spirits, with a similar refrain about not allowing the devils to speak.', 'parallel', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 34, 41, 3, 12, 12, 'cast out many devils', 'Jesus'' Authority and Secrecy', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' authority over evil. In Mark 1:34, he casts out devils, while in Mark 3:12, he commands them not to reveal his identity.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 34, 40, 4, 23, 23, 'healed many that were sick', 'Healing Ministry of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' role in healing. Mark highlights his healing of many sick and casting out devils, while Matthew describes his healing of all manner of sickness and disease among the people.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 34, 44, 16, 16, 18, 'cast out many devils', 'Healing and Exorcism Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of casting out spirits. In Mark, Jesus does not allow the devils to speak, while Paul commands a spirit to leave a possessed girl. This connection highlights the authority of both figures over unclean spirits.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 34, 41, 1, 25, 25, 'cast out many devils', 'Jesus'' Authority Over Demons', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' authority in casting out devils. In Mark 1:25, Jesus directly rebukes a demon, while in Mark 1:34, he does not allow the devils to speak, indicating his control over them.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 42, 6, 12, 12, 'solitary place', 'Prayer in Solitary Places', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer in solitude, highlighting Jesus'' commitment to seeking God away from distractions. The solitary nature of His prayer in Mark parallels the all-night prayer in Luke, showcasing a consistent theme of devotion.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 42, 22, 39, 46, 'a solitary place, and there prayed', 'Prayer in Solitude', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer in solitude. In Mark, Jesus seeks a solitary place to pray, while in Luke, he withdraws from his disciples to pray earnestly before his crucifixion.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 49, 6, 18, 18, 'there prayed', 'Connection of Prayer Practices', 'This connection highlights the importance of prayer in both passages. Mark emphasizes Jesus'' practice of solitary prayer, while Ephesians encourages believers to pray always and with perseverance.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 19, 5, 3, 3, 'in the morning', 'Morning Prayer Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of morning prayer. Mark highlights Jesus rising early to pray, while Psalms expresses a commitment to direct prayer to God in the morning.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 58, 5, 7, 7, 'there prayed', 'Prayer in Times of Need', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer in both passages. Mark 1:35 describes Jesus praying in solitude, while Hebrews 5:7 emphasizes his prayers and supplications during times of distress.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 43, 6, 15, 15, 'departed into a solitary place', 'Jesus'' Solitude and Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' practice of seeking solitude. In Mark, he goes to a solitary place to pray, while in John, he departs alone to a mountain, highlighting his need for solitude amidst public pressure.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 35, 40, 14, 23, 23, 'solitary place', 'Jesus'' Solitary Prayer Practices', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' practice of seeking solitude to pray. In Mark, he rises early to a solitary place, while in Matthew, he goes up into a mountain apart to pray.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 37, 43, 12, 19, 19, 'All men seek for thee', 'Public Attention on Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the widespread interest in Jesus. In Mark, people are actively seeking him, while in John, the Pharisees note that ''the world is gone after him.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 37, 38, 11, 11, 11, 'All men seek for thee', 'Seeking the Word of the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking, as both passages reflect a longing for divine guidance. In Mark, the people seek Jesus, while in Zechariah, the poor of the flock recognize the word of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 37, 41, 1, 5, 5, 'All men seek for thee', 'Public Response to Jesus'' Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the widespread attention Jesus received. In Mark 1:5, people from Judea and Jerusalem sought out John for baptism, while in Mark 1:37, they express their desire to find Jesus, indicating a growing recognition of his significance.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 37, 43, 3, 26, 26, 'all men seek for thee', 'Seeking Jesus and Baptism', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that ''all men'' are seeking Jesus or coming to him. This connection highlights the growing recognition of Jesus'' significance and the impact of his ministry as noted by those around him.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 37, 43, 11, 48, 48, 'All men seek for thee', 'Public Interest in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the widespread attention Jesus receives. In Mark, people are actively seeking him, while in John, there is concern that if he is left alone, many will believe in him.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 38, 42, 4, 43, 43, 'for therefore came I forth', 'Preaching Mission Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of preaching in multiple locations. They highlight the purpose of Jesus'' mission to spread the message of the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 38, 23, 61, 1, 3, 'that I may preach there also', 'Connection of Preaching Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of preaching good news. Both passages emphasize the mission to proclaim and bring hope to those in need.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 38, 43, 17, 8, 8, 'for therefore came I forth', 'Mission and Authority of Jesus', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' purpose in preaching and the authority of his words. Both passages emphasize the importance of Jesus'' mission and the belief in his divine origin.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 38, 42, 2, 49, 49, 'that I may preach there also', 'Purpose of Jesus'' Mission', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' commitment to his divine purpose. In Mark, he states he must preach, while in Luke, he indicates he must be about his Father''s business.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 1, 38, 43, 16, 28, 28, 'for therefore came I forth', 'Mission and Origin of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' mission. Mark highlights His intent to preach, while John reflects on His origin from the Father, indicating a divine purpose in His coming into the world.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
